{{!< default}}

<!-- default.hbs already includes {{> particle-morph}} once, globally,
     outside <main> — this file used to include it a second time here,
     which meant every post using this template loaded the whole particle
     system's script twice. Two copies of the same inline <script> both
     declaring top-level `let attempts` throws a SyntaxError (classic
     <script> tags share one global lexical scope), which silently crashed
     the ENTIRE script — including the post/about/contact/work exclusion
     check at the top of particle-morph.hbs, so particles never actually
     hid on any post using this template. -->
<div class="page-content"></div>
